WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.878 --> 00:00:03.879
[pigeons cooing]

2
00:00:05.048 --> 00:00:07.050
[sirens wailing]

3
00:00:08.301 --> 00:00:10.053
[horn honks]

4
00:00:18.895 --> 00:00:22.274
- [Chapman] Christ. what just happened?
- [Jackson] I just saved your arse.

5
00:00:22.274 --> 00:00:24.234
It was about to be
handed to you on a platter.

6
00:00:24.234 --> 00:00:26.987
I'm out of shape.
Gotta get back in the gym. [sighs]

7
00:00:26.987 --> 00:00:28.697
[Jackson] Did you recognize that guy?

8
00:00:28.697 --> 00:00:31.908
No. Foreign. A fucking pro.

9
00:00:31.908 --> 00:00:34.286
[Marcus] Took four of us and
a moving vehicle and he still walked away.

10
00:00:34.286 --> 00:00:35.453
Well. not quite four of us.

11
00:00:35.453 --> 00:00:37.956
These two crusties only count as one.
I'm not sure you count at all.

12
00:00:37.956 --> 00:00:39.791
- What's her problem?
- [Jackson] Oh. everyone.

13
00:00:39.791 --> 00:00:41.376
- Tell me about Lavande.
- [Chapman] Lavande?

14
00:00:41.376 --> 00:00:45.130
[Jackson] Yeah. before you were head Dog
you were David Cartwright's bagman.

15
00:00:45.130 --> 00:00:46.882
- He sent you there.
- Oh. Christ.

16
00:00:49.885 --> 00:00:51.595
This is about Les Arbres.

17
00:00:52.971 --> 00:00:53.972
French trees?

18
00:00:53.972 --> 00:00:57.017
It's a compound. Off-grid.
They're bad people.

19
00:00:57.517 --> 00:00:59.311
Dangerous. Professional killers.

20
00:00:59.311 --> 00:01:01.438
I don't want the Park
anywhere near this. Jackson.

21
00:01:01.438 --> 00:01:04.983
I'm exposed. If I walk into the Park and
tell them what I did. I'm not walking out.

22
00:01:04.983 --> 00:01:06.359
Why? What did you do?

23
00:01:08.778 --> 00:01:10.488
I'll do the debrief back in the office.

24
00:01:11.364 --> 00:01:12.949
Oh. yeah. Not in front of the kids.

25
00:01:12.949 --> 00:01:14.034
Fair enough.

26
00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:22.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

27
00:01:47.901 --> 00:01:49.903
[elevator door closes]

28
00:02:15.095 --> 00:02:16.096
[Frank groans]

29
00:02:23.478 --> 00:02:25.146
[grunts]

30
00:02:26.439 --> 00:02:29.943
It's a bit of overkill
on the security. no?

31
00:02:29.943 --> 00:02:31.695
I thought we were just talking.

32
00:02:32.237 --> 00:02:33.238
So talk.

33
00:02:34.072 --> 00:02:39.661
Your Highness.
let me start by offering an apology.

34
00:02:39.661 --> 00:02:42.664
Westacres did not go according to plan.

35
00:02:42.664 --> 00:02:45.125
Not a great start to
our working relationship.

36
00:02:45.125 --> 00:02:49.087
Mr. Harkness. I have people
in my country's security apparatus

37
00:02:49.087 --> 00:02:50.213
who can do what you do.

38
00:02:50.922 --> 00:02:53.550
The reason I outsourced this job to you

39
00:02:53.550 --> 00:02:57.053
was because I was told
you were discreet and left no trace.

40
00:02:57.053 --> 00:03:01.641
Well. in normal circumstances. yes.
That is exactly what I do.

41
00:03:02.392 --> 00:03:06.605
Unfortunately... [sighs]
...there was a-a confluence of events--

42
00:03:06.605 --> 00:03:08.023
What did I pay you for?

43
00:03:10.567 --> 00:03:11.526
A hit.

44
00:03:12.402 --> 00:03:16.489
To look like an accident
in the Westacres parking lot.

45
00:03:16.489 --> 00:03:17.824
You blew it up.

46
00:03:17.824 --> 00:03:20.952
No. I did not.
That was part of the problem.

47
00:03:20.952 --> 00:03:24.247
There was a weak link in my organization
that I should have spotted.

48
00:03:24.247 --> 00:03:26.082
Next time I'll be more hands-on.

49
00:03:26.082 --> 00:03:27.208
Next time?

50
00:03:27.208 --> 00:03:31.213
I will fulfill the contract at a discount.

51
00:03:31.213 --> 00:03:32.547
No. you will not.

52
00:03:35.967 --> 00:03:37.177
So...

53
00:03:40.805 --> 00:03:41.723
Why am I here?

54
00:03:42.724 --> 00:03:46.895
If the British government found out
we had anything to do with Westacres.

55
00:03:46.895 --> 00:03:49.731
- it would cause untold diplomatic damage.
- [speaks indistinctly]

56
00:03:50.232 --> 00:03:52.525
[prince] We want to erase anything
that links us to the bomb.

57
00:03:52.525 --> 00:03:57.072
[Frank] Fine. How about
we cut the theatrics. yeah?

58
00:03:57.072 --> 00:03:59.449
[chuckling] And you tell me
what you really want--

59
00:03:59.449 --> 00:04:00.951
I want this to have never happened.

60
00:04:01.868 --> 00:04:03.453
I want to erase the trail.

61
00:04:03.453 --> 00:04:05.830
- Come on. You're not gonna erase me.
- [tools clattering]

62
00:04:05.830 --> 00:04:08.875
I know how much noise you make
when you cut up a body.

63
00:04:08.875 --> 00:04:11.878
That is why we have taken out
the floor above and the floor below.

64
00:04:11.878 --> 00:04:13.380
Okay. Full refund.

65
00:04:14.673 --> 00:04:17.091
Next five jobs for free.

66
00:04:18.300 --> 00:04:20.303
Oh. holy shit. [sighs]

67
00:04:20.303 --> 00:04:21.930
- [drill whirring]
- [groans]

68
00:04:21.930 --> 00:04:24.266
Other people know about Westacres.

69
00:04:24.266 --> 00:04:27.394
You will be paralyzed.
but awake throughout.

70
00:04:28.270 --> 00:04:29.563
I will enjoy watching.

71
00:04:30.981 --> 00:04:34.442
Well. kill me. but the people
who know are still out there.

72
00:04:36.444 --> 00:04:37.445
[prince] Who?

73
00:04:39.114 --> 00:04:40.615
Ex-service. [sighs]

74
00:04:40.615 --> 00:04:42.325
By the time you get the names out of me.

75
00:04:42.325 --> 00:04:44.786
they'll have gone to ground
or fled to the Park.

76
00:04:44.786 --> 00:04:47.247
Come on. I need this to go away too.

77
00:04:47.247 --> 00:04:49.583
I want them dead by midnight.

78
00:04:50.625 --> 00:04:52.002
After that you work for me.

79
00:04:52.878 --> 00:04:53.879
Sure.

80
00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:58.758
[Frank] <i>I'll bring the old fucks
back here and chop 'em up myself.</i>

81
00:05:10.061 --> 00:05:13.064
["Strange Game" playing]

82
00:06:12.707 --> 00:06:13.750
[Chapman] Shit.

83
00:06:13.750 --> 00:06:14.918
Dogs. Fuck.

84
00:06:14.918 --> 00:06:16.044
What do they want?

85
00:06:16.711 --> 00:06:19.422
Me probably. I keep
dicking their boss around.

86
00:06:20.382 --> 00:06:22.968
Uh. jump on the phone
and see if they're in the building.

87
00:06:22.968 --> 00:06:25.220
- [music playing on radio]
- [phone buzzes]

88
00:06:29.349 --> 00:06:30.850
[Shirley] <i>Have they come in?</i>

89
00:06:30.850 --> 00:06:32.269
No.

90
00:06:32.269 --> 00:06:34.271
They smelled the scent
of the big dog on the door.

91
00:06:34.271 --> 00:06:36.731
Earlier today you literally
let the head Dog back in.

92
00:06:36.731 --> 00:06:37.941
I was honey-trapped.

93
00:06:38.441 --> 00:06:41.778
My one weakness is beautiful women.
which is why you're no threat to me.

94
00:06:41.778 --> 00:06:43.405
- [Shirley coughing]
- [line clicks]

95
00:06:43.405 --> 00:06:44.614
They're hanging outside.

96
00:06:44.614 --> 00:06:47.200
- Ho remains the dickhead's dickhead.
- Okay. [sighs]

97
00:06:47.784 --> 00:06:49.035
Uh. wait here.

98
00:06:49.661 --> 00:06:52.664
If they take me in
and Flyte hasn't nabbed Cartwright.

99
00:06:52.664 --> 00:06:55.166
keep him safe and away from them
until River shows.

100
00:06:55.917 --> 00:06:59.671
And-- And you.
I hope your flight fund's up to date.

101
00:07:12.183 --> 00:07:13.518
- You coming up?
- No.

102
00:07:13.518 --> 00:07:14.603
Am I getting in?

103
00:07:14.603 --> 00:07:15.812
No. I've just had it valeted.

104
00:07:15.812 --> 00:07:17.439
[stammers] Well. I can't stand here.

105
00:07:17.439 --> 00:07:19.024
- I'm getting soaked.
- [sighs]

106
00:07:19.941 --> 00:07:21.109
I'm going up.

107
00:07:33.163 --> 00:07:35.123
[inhales sharply] You could've called.

108
00:07:35.123 --> 00:07:36.291
Saved you the trip.

109
00:07:36.291 --> 00:07:38.668
- I did. More than once.
- Really?

110
00:07:41.504 --> 00:07:42.881
Ah. yeah. So you did.

111
00:07:43.632 --> 00:07:45.967
Apologies. What? You just
parked up there on the off chance?

112
00:07:45.967 --> 00:07:47.928
You lied to Flyte.

113
00:07:47.928 --> 00:07:50.513
- Yeah.
- The dead man was an assassin.

114
00:07:51.431 --> 00:07:54.017
You know. that's why
you've got a career in espionage.

115
00:07:54.017 --> 00:07:56.311
Why would someone want to
kill David Cartwright now?

116
00:07:56.311 --> 00:07:57.395
Have you met him?

117
00:07:57.896 --> 00:08:00.315
I-- [stammers] I don't know why you're
bothering me with all of this.

118
00:08:00.315 --> 00:08:03.693
Shouldn't you be out there
making sure no more bombs go off?

119
00:08:03.693 --> 00:08:05.695
Where's River Cartwright?
And what is he up to?

120
00:08:05.695 --> 00:08:09.199
He is in France.
retracing the assassin's steps.

121
00:08:09.199 --> 00:08:11.284
I have no way of contacting him.

122
00:08:11.284 --> 00:08:13.036
And I assume he's hidden
his grandpa somewhere?

123
00:08:13.036 --> 00:08:16.498
Well. I'd like to think so. but as I say.
I have no way of contacting him.

124
00:08:16.498 --> 00:08:19.459
I told Flyte that he was at
Catherine Standish's.

125
00:08:19.459 --> 00:08:20.585
just to get rid of her.

126
00:08:20.585 --> 00:08:21.962
[stammers] What?

127
00:08:22.504 --> 00:08:25.715
What. she not-- she not tell you. did she?
That's a bit disrespectful.

128
00:08:25.715 --> 00:08:28.635
If either of the Cartwrights show.
I want to be the first to know.

129
00:08:29.970 --> 00:08:32.556
And I tell you this
out of the goodness of my heart?

130
00:08:32.556 --> 00:08:34.849
[chuckles] What goodness? What heart?

131
00:09:00.792 --> 00:09:02.168
Sure you don't want any tea?

132
00:09:02.168 --> 00:09:03.253
No. thank you.

133
00:09:04.045 --> 00:09:05.046
Something stronger?

134
00:09:08.383 --> 00:09:09.593
I meant coffee.

135
00:09:13.763 --> 00:09:15.932
He does that. No one knows why.

136
00:09:16.850 --> 00:09:18.101
Has anyone thought to ask him?

137
00:09:18.101 --> 00:09:20.520
Well. it's quite hard
to find the right moment.

138
00:09:21.563 --> 00:09:23.690
He's trying to block something out.

139
00:09:24.482 --> 00:09:27.110
Can't I send him out
to help in the search?

140
00:09:27.110 --> 00:09:30.363
You're not in charge of anyone.
You don't work here at the moment.

141
00:09:30.363 --> 00:09:33.074
What do you mean at the moment?
I'm not coming back.

142
00:09:33.074 --> 00:09:37.996
Well. there will be a vacancy.
because I'm going back to the Park.

143
00:09:38.622 --> 00:09:39.956
[door opens]

144
00:09:42.709 --> 00:09:43.710
[door closes]

145
00:09:49.841 --> 00:09:50.842
Oi!

146
00:09:52.761 --> 00:09:55.430
Great work. Longridge. [laughs]

147
00:09:58.391 --> 00:10:00.852
[chuckles] What a dickhead.

148
00:10:00.852 --> 00:10:02.938
[footsteps approaching]

149
00:10:05.232 --> 00:10:06.233
[door opens]

150
00:10:08.777 --> 00:10:10.570
- Where is he?
- [Marcus] Catherine?

151
00:10:11.154 --> 00:10:12.864
- Are you back?
- No.

152
00:10:12.864 --> 00:10:14.824
Uh. David Cartwright. you know.
the Old Bastard.

153
00:10:14.824 --> 00:10:17.035
is he upstairs or have you
shut him in the fridge?

154
00:10:17.035 --> 00:10:18.286
She lost him.

155
00:10:19.120 --> 00:10:21.623
- I moved him before Flyte got there.
- Where?

156
00:10:21.623 --> 00:10:23.041
- [Catherine] My neighbor's.
- And?

157
00:10:23.917 --> 00:10:26.419
- He got out.
- Oh. for fuck's sake. Standish.

158
00:10:26.419 --> 00:10:28.672
You know. you wouldn't have
lost him if he was a bottle of gin.

159
00:10:28.672 --> 00:10:31.216
- [Moira chuckles]
- He wants to speak to First Desk.

160
00:10:31.216 --> 00:10:33.093
so we think he's heading for the Park.

161
00:10:33.093 --> 00:10:34.636
Louisa is nearby. in case he shows.

162
00:10:34.636 --> 00:10:36.555
I came here to get
some more people onto it.

163
00:10:36.555 --> 00:10:39.558
Now. he might use a side entrance
or ask a policeman to get him in.

164
00:10:39.558 --> 00:10:41.810
Jesus Christ. Jackson.
if he talks I'm in shit up to my nose.

165
00:10:41.810 --> 00:10:43.979
Yeah. yeah. He's out of his fucking mind.

166
00:10:43.979 --> 00:10:45.146
How's he gonna find the Park?

167
00:10:45.146 --> 00:10:47.023
He'll be wandering
the streets like a lost dog.

168
00:10:47.023 --> 00:10:51.069
Scratch and Sniff. you get out there
and stake out the surrounding area.

169
00:10:51.069 --> 00:10:53.405
- I'll go with them.
- Oh. what? So you can lose him again?

170
00:10:53.947 --> 00:10:55.073
No. thank you.

171
00:10:55.907 --> 00:10:57.033
- Upstairs.
- [door opens]

172
00:10:57.742 --> 00:10:59.661
- Sit in on this.
- Why?

173
00:10:59.661 --> 00:11:00.829
[Jackson] Or don't then.

174
00:11:18.680 --> 00:11:20.098
[sighs]

175
00:11:25.478 --> 00:11:26.646
[Frank] You're late.

176
00:11:27.147 --> 00:11:28.899
Had to get patched up.

177
00:11:28.899 --> 00:11:31.026
- Where?
- Hip and shoulder.

178
00:11:31.693 --> 00:11:34.321
I mean. where did you go
to get patched up?

179
00:11:34.321 --> 00:11:35.947
- Doctor.
- [phone buzzes]

180
00:11:38.909 --> 00:11:41.578
Bertrand's passport is on the move.

181
00:11:41.578 --> 00:11:45.957
which means River Cartwright
is coming back from France.

182
00:11:48.335 --> 00:11:50.754
So will this doctor keep quiet? [sighs]

183
00:11:51.379 --> 00:11:53.506
When I left him he was not making a sound.

184
00:11:53.506 --> 00:11:55.508
And Chapman taken care of?

185
00:11:56.718 --> 00:11:57.719
He had help.

186
00:11:58.470 --> 00:11:59.471
Who?

187
00:12:01.139 --> 00:12:02.140
I don't know.

188
00:12:05.977 --> 00:12:08.146
This the shoulder that got hurt?

189
00:12:09.189 --> 00:12:11.608
[gasps. grunting]

190
00:12:11.608 --> 00:12:13.818
The clients are very unhappy.

191
00:12:13.818 --> 00:12:15.862
- If we don't take out the targets...
- [sighs]

192
00:12:15.862 --> 00:12:17.781
...we get taken out ourselves.

193
00:12:17.781 --> 00:12:20.200
- So do you think you can get this done?
- [groans]

194
00:12:20.200 --> 00:12:22.494
[shivers] Yes. sir.

195
00:12:22.494 --> 00:12:24.037
[grunts. groans]

196
00:12:27.999 --> 00:12:29.000
Eat.

197
00:12:33.505 --> 00:12:35.340
- [grunts]
- Maybe the people who helped Chapman

198
00:12:35.340 --> 00:12:36.841
are helping Cartwright too.

199
00:12:36.841 --> 00:12:40.762
So make sure Chapman talks
before you silence him.

200
00:12:40.762 --> 00:12:42.597
How do I find him?

201
00:12:43.181 --> 00:12:44.891
He'll have gone to ground.

202
00:12:44.891 --> 00:12:46.434
Won't want to be caught by us.

203
00:12:46.977 --> 00:12:48.478
Won't want to be
caught by the Park either.

204
00:12:48.478 --> 00:12:50.814
Come on. These old fucks
are so predictable.

205
00:12:50.814 --> 00:12:53.900
What does a spook do when he's spooked?

206
00:12:53.900 --> 00:12:57.779
He grabs his flight fund and he flies.

207
00:12:58.947 --> 00:13:00.657
Oh. you know where it is?

208
00:13:10.834 --> 00:13:12.294
[Jackson] So France. [sighs]

209
00:13:12.294 --> 00:13:13.962
- Just the one trip?
- [Chapman] Yeah.

210
00:13:13.962 --> 00:13:16.423
[clears throat] He sent me
in for an extraction.

211
00:13:17.340 --> 00:13:19.467
- No details. [sighs]
- That usual?

212
00:13:19.467 --> 00:13:21.970
- That lack of intel?
- Well. you know what he was like.

213
00:13:21.970 --> 00:13:23.597
[Jackson grunts] I do.

214
00:13:24.681 --> 00:13:26.641
There's a reason he's known
as the Old Bastard.

215
00:13:26.641 --> 00:13:29.060
[stammers] Well. back then
it was just the Bastard.

216
00:13:29.936 --> 00:13:30.937
[Chapman chuckles]

217
00:13:33.732 --> 00:13:35.108
I picked up a car in Dover.

218
00:13:36.109 --> 00:13:37.485
He told me not to poke around in it.

219
00:13:37.485 --> 00:13:38.612
I was glad I didn't.

220
00:13:38.612 --> 00:13:41.364
because I wouldn't have gone through
customs if I'd known what was in there.

221
00:13:42.324 --> 00:13:44.910
When I got to Lavande.
they took the car apart.

222
00:13:45.911 --> 00:13:46.995
[Jackson] <i>Who?</i>

223
00:13:48.204 --> 00:13:49.331
[Chapman] <i>Mercenaries.</i>

224
00:14:05.722 --> 00:14:07.182
I only spoke to the leader.

225
00:14:07.182 --> 00:14:09.017
Yank. Didn't get a name.

226
00:14:10.227 --> 00:14:11.478
<i>Scary fucker.</i>

227
00:14:12.187 --> 00:14:13.271
What did they find?

228
00:14:14.648 --> 00:14:20.403
[Chapman] <i>Cash. munitions.
C-4. detonators and IDs.</i>

229
00:14:25.450 --> 00:14:26.451
<i>Cold bodies.</i>

230
00:14:34.334 --> 00:14:39.172
[inhales sharply] I don't suppose you--
you remember any of the names?

231
00:14:39.172 --> 00:14:40.924
No. I didn't get to see them close up.

232
00:14:42.300 --> 00:14:45.845
I would bet money
on one of them being Robert Winters.

233
00:14:46.638 --> 00:14:47.889
[Chapman] Like I said. I didn't see.

234
00:14:47.889 --> 00:14:49.641
[Jackson] What'd you get in return?

235
00:14:50.517 --> 00:14:52.018
Who did you extract?

236
00:14:52.018 --> 00:14:54.813
A girl. [sighs] A young woman.

237
00:14:59.359 --> 00:15:01.236
[exhales deeply] Place was fucked up.

238
00:15:04.114 --> 00:15:07.742
<i>These women and kids
hanging around all these psychos.</i>

239
00:15:09.202 --> 00:15:11.454
[whispers indistinctly]

240
00:15:12.914 --> 00:15:14.332
She didn't wanna go.

241
00:15:15.542 --> 00:15:17.377
<i>Fuck knows why she wanted to stay.</i>

242
00:15:24.467 --> 00:15:25.468
[Chapman sighs]

243
00:15:26.720 --> 00:15:27.762
[Jackson] <i>Who was she?</i>

244
00:15:28.513 --> 00:15:29.639
[Chapman] <i>No idea.</i>

245
00:15:29.639 --> 00:15:32.767
[clears throat] <i>Couldn't get
a word out of her all the way back.</i>

246
00:15:34.436 --> 00:15:37.063
<i>I stopped off for petrol in the UK.
She gave me the slip.</i>

247
00:15:40.191 --> 00:15:42.485
[sighs] And how did Cartwright react?

248
00:15:42.986 --> 00:15:43.987
He didn't.

249
00:15:46.364 --> 00:15:49.034
It was like he was resigned to it.
as if he'd expected her to run.

250
00:15:49.534 --> 00:15:51.369
When I reported to the old building. he...

251
00:15:52.245 --> 00:15:54.247
Well. I thought
he'd lose his shit with me and fire me.

252
00:15:54.247 --> 00:15:55.498
But I was fine with that--

253
00:15:55.498 --> 00:15:59.169
You said he wanted to
report to First Desk.

254
00:15:59.169 --> 00:16:00.253
Yes.

255
00:16:02.088 --> 00:16:03.757
No. he's not going to the Park.

256
00:16:03.757 --> 00:16:05.884
- That's where First Desk is.
- Not in his mind.

257
00:16:17.270 --> 00:16:19.314
[breathing heavily]

258
00:16:19.314 --> 00:16:21.608
- Oh! Apologies.
- [passerby] Fuck's sake.

259
00:16:25.987 --> 00:16:27.989
[breathing heavily]

260
00:16:35.705 --> 00:16:37.832
- I know you are. I know you are.
- [chuckles]

261
00:16:37.832 --> 00:16:40.126
- All right. Trying to get away from me?
- [chuckles]

262
00:16:40.126 --> 00:16:42.128
- Yeah. [chuckles]
- Okay. Thank you.

263
00:16:42.128 --> 00:16:44.297
All right. Joshua? Nice to see you.

264
00:16:45.257 --> 00:16:48.218
Hi. All right. What's in the updates
that we've got here. guys?

265
00:16:48.843 --> 00:16:50.554
- That's really good work.
- [knocks on door]

266
00:16:50.554 --> 00:16:51.930
Keep us updated. will you?

267
00:16:51.930 --> 00:16:53.765
- Come in.
- [door opens]

268
00:16:59.020 --> 00:17:02.065
Take away the good looks
and there's really nothing there.

269
00:17:03.358 --> 00:17:05.651
- [sighs]
- [Flyte] Sorry? [chuckles]

270
00:17:08.280 --> 00:17:10.532
[laughs]

271
00:17:10.532 --> 00:17:12.659
- I didn't mean you.
- [phone buzzes]

272
00:17:12.659 --> 00:17:14.828
Although you are turning out to be
a bit of a disappointment.

273
00:17:14.828 --> 00:17:17.205
- Do you want-- Do you want to get that?
- No. [chuckles]

274
00:17:17.789 --> 00:17:20.708
The reason your predecessor
and I parted ways.

275
00:17:21.458 --> 00:17:24.212
apart from his encounter
with a concrete block.

276
00:17:25.463 --> 00:17:27.215
was lack of communication.

277
00:17:30.468 --> 00:17:32.220
Is there anything you want to tell me?

278
00:17:35.599 --> 00:17:38.268
River Cartwright is still alive.
Lamb misidentified the body.

279
00:17:38.268 --> 00:17:39.185
Yeah.

280
00:17:39.185 --> 00:17:43.481
I warned you about Lamb. which is
why I checked the blood results myself.

281
00:17:44.232 --> 00:17:47.402
But why did you withhold
the crucial update

282
00:17:47.402 --> 00:17:50.530
- that a dead agent wasn't quite so dead?
- I apologize for the lack of updates.

283
00:17:50.530 --> 00:17:53.116
I wanted to shake Lamb down
and have some answers for you.

284
00:17:53.116 --> 00:17:56.369
- [laughing] Oh. And how did that go?
- I think you know the answer to that.

285
00:17:56.369 --> 00:17:58.747
Well. I've heard Lamb's version.
I'd like to hear yours.

286
00:17:58.747 --> 00:18:02.000
He sent me to Catherine Standish's
where David Cartwright wasn't.

287
00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.627
That's Lamb.

288
00:18:03.627 --> 00:18:05.754
You're supposed to be a straight shooter.

289
00:18:05.754 --> 00:18:08.632
You go behind my back one more time
and you are out.

290
00:18:09.216 --> 00:18:10.217
Understood?

291
00:18:11.760 --> 00:18:12.886
Yes. ma'am.

292
00:18:12.886 --> 00:18:15.180
- Bring me the Cartwrights.
- Yes. ma'am.

293
00:18:19.309 --> 00:18:22.020
In the Met we were always told to
follow the evidence wherever it leads.

294
00:18:22.020 --> 00:18:24.189
You're not in the Met now. You're at MI5.

295
00:18:24.189 --> 00:18:25.899
I assumed the same principles would apply.

296
00:18:25.899 --> 00:18:29.527
Emma. contrary to what
you might think. I like you.

297
00:18:30.237 --> 00:18:33.907
We've both had to work three times as hard
as any man to get to the same job.

298
00:18:33.907 --> 00:18:35.992
So know that I have
your best interests at heart

299
00:18:35.992 --> 00:18:38.411
when I tell you
that the severance package.

300
00:18:38.411 --> 00:18:39.913
- if you resign...
- [phone buzzing]

301
00:18:39.913 --> 00:18:42.499
...is far more generous
than should I fire you.

302
00:18:42.499 --> 00:18:43.959
Would you like to write your letter now?

303
00:18:43.959 --> 00:18:46.127
Ma'am. that's the old building calling.

304
00:18:49.506 --> 00:18:51.383
You mentioned the old building.

305
00:18:51.383 --> 00:18:54.844
- That's where he's headed.
- Oh. you need to call Louisa.

306
00:18:54.844 --> 00:18:56.304
Stand her down.

307
00:18:56.304 --> 00:18:58.056
No. no. I didn't send her there.

308
00:18:58.056 --> 00:18:59.933
You sent Marcus and Shirley.

309
00:18:59.933 --> 00:19:02.227
- Will you call them?
- No. you call them.

310
00:19:03.144 --> 00:19:06.606
- River has my phone.
- Oh. fuck. For crying out loud.

311
00:19:06.606 --> 00:19:07.857
Here. Take it.

312
00:19:09.901 --> 00:19:12.070
- [Flyte] <i>And you're positive it's him?</i>
- [concierge] Yes. ma'am.

313
00:19:12.070 --> 00:19:14.281
[Flyte] <i>Okay. We're on our way there now.</i>

314
00:19:14.281 --> 00:19:15.407
<i>Don't let him leave the lobby.</i>

315
00:19:15.407 --> 00:19:16.366
Of course.

316
00:19:17.117 --> 00:19:18.702
We'll do our best to keep him here.

317
00:19:18.702 --> 00:19:21.121
- Is he being a problem?
- <i>No. no. no. He's fine.</i>

318
00:19:21.121 --> 00:19:22.247
He's just confused.

319
00:19:22.831 --> 00:19:25.250
I told him someone
will be here for him soon.

320
00:19:25.250 --> 00:19:26.877
<i>Good. We won't be long.</i>

321
00:19:31.131 --> 00:19:33.133
[phone buzzing]

322
00:19:35.594 --> 00:19:37.012
- [Catherine] <i>Louisa.</i>
- Yeah. hi.

323
00:19:37.012 --> 00:19:39.639
- Still no sign of him.
- <i>Uh. well. there won't be.</i>

324
00:19:39.639 --> 00:19:41.141
<i>We think he's heading to the old building.</i>

325
00:19:41.141 --> 00:19:42.559
Oh. shit.

326
00:19:42.559 --> 00:19:43.685
<i>What?</i>

327
00:19:49.232 --> 00:19:50.233
[Louisa] <i>Flyte just left.</i>

328
00:19:50.233 --> 00:19:51.985
- <i>Oh.</i>
- Maybe someone called him in.

329
00:19:51.985 --> 00:19:55.071
<i>No-- Well. Marcus and Shirley
are heading to you. okay?</i>

330
00:19:55.572 --> 00:19:56.948
Oh. yeah. Got 'em.

331
00:19:58.491 --> 00:20:00.076
Flyte's on her way there too.

332
00:20:00.076 --> 00:20:02.370
The receptionist must have called them.

333
00:20:02.871 --> 00:20:04.789
- It's a hotel now?
- Yes. Very posh.

334
00:20:04.789 --> 00:20:08.335
Yeah. the detention cells
are now massage suites.

335
00:20:08.335 --> 00:20:09.836
They're still
full of Russians. ironically.

336
00:20:09.836 --> 00:20:11.796
Yeah. well. if the Park
get to him before we do.

337
00:20:11.796 --> 00:20:13.173
I'll be the one in a bloody cell.

338
00:20:13.173 --> 00:20:15.508
River will never forgive me
if I don't protect David.

339
00:20:15.508 --> 00:20:17.427
Oh. your feelings or my freedom?

340
00:20:17.427 --> 00:20:19.095
Pardon me for not giving a shit.

341
00:20:19.846 --> 00:20:21.556
Nice to see you haven't changed then.

342
00:20:27.979 --> 00:20:29.981
[chattering]

343
00:20:43.411 --> 00:20:45.288
[Diana] We've located David Cartwright.

344
00:20:45.288 --> 00:20:47.123
Oh. Is he okay?

345
00:20:47.624 --> 00:20:49.793
Physically. um. he's fine.
as far as I know.

346
00:20:49.793 --> 00:20:51.503
Mentally he's not the man he was.

347
00:20:52.128 --> 00:20:54.422
He's waiting for First Desk
over at the old building.

348
00:20:55.006 --> 00:20:56.675
I'll debrief him myself when he gets here.

349
00:20:56.675 --> 00:20:59.302
Actually. I. um--
I have some news for you too

350
00:20:59.302 --> 00:21:00.595
- about his grandson.
- Mmm?

351
00:21:01.221 --> 00:21:03.974
Yes. I was waiting to update you on that.

352
00:21:03.974 --> 00:21:06.226
Oh. were you? Well. I'm all ears.

353
00:21:06.226 --> 00:21:07.769
Let's do that now. shall we?

354
00:21:16.152 --> 00:21:17.195
[door beeps. opens]

355
00:21:17.195 --> 00:21:18.446
[Diana] Oh. Giti.

356
00:21:18.989 --> 00:21:20.323
Should HR be present?

357
00:21:20.323 --> 00:21:23.243
- [laughs] That's funny. That's funny.
- [door closes]

358
00:21:23.243 --> 00:21:25.954
No. Actually I gave Giti permission
to check the archives.

359
00:21:25.954 --> 00:21:30.125
Just to see that there weren't any more
pesky glitches in the cold body program.

360
00:21:30.125 --> 00:21:32.794
But unfortunately. she found one.

361
00:21:32.794 --> 00:21:34.421
Uh. Adam Lockhead.

362
00:21:36.089 --> 00:21:38.300
That name is irrelevant
to anything that's going on out there.

363
00:21:38.300 --> 00:21:39.467
[Claude] Well. I think not.

364
00:21:39.467 --> 00:21:43.847
Here's a photo Adam Lockhead submitted to
the passport office for his last renewal.

365
00:21:44.931 --> 00:21:47.642
This. uh. look familiar. does it?

366
00:21:49.185 --> 00:21:50.312
- Yeah.
- Oh. Jesus.

367
00:21:50.312 --> 00:21:51.938
Yeah. he is back from the dead.

368
00:21:51.938 --> 00:21:54.232
Spit of River Cartwright.
wouldn't you say?

369
00:21:54.816 --> 00:21:55.817
[sighs]

370
00:21:55.817 --> 00:22:00.030
Cartwright left his ID on the body
and he must have taken Adam Lockhead's.

371
00:22:00.030 --> 00:22:01.197
I'd say so.

372
00:22:01.197 --> 00:22:02.616
Well. it tallies.

373
00:22:02.616 --> 00:22:04.409
Adam Lockhead
entered the country from France

374
00:22:04.409 --> 00:22:06.453
the day before
the attempt on David Cartwright.

375
00:22:06.453 --> 00:22:08.580
He then went back to France
the day after David disappeared.

376
00:22:08.580 --> 00:22:11.458
[Claude] So we've got one cold body
responsible for Westacres.

377
00:22:11.458 --> 00:22:13.793
Another attempted a hit
on the éminence grise of the Service.

378
00:22:13.793 --> 00:22:15.795
Oh. God alone knows
what's gonna happen next.

379
00:22:15.795 --> 00:22:17.339
We're up to our necks in this!

380
00:22:17.339 --> 00:22:19.716
Giti. get this ID over to Interpol
and the DGSE.

381
00:22:20.550 --> 00:22:22.135
Do it somewhere other than this.

382
00:22:29.142 --> 00:22:31.561
Look. we can't pretend
that these are some sins from the past

383
00:22:31.561 --> 00:22:33.313
and just brush them under the carpet.

384
00:22:33.313 --> 00:22:36.358
This is playing out now.
Right now in the present.

385
00:22:36.358 --> 00:22:39.569
First steps. I debrief David Cartwright
and then we go--

386
00:22:39.569 --> 00:22:40.528
No.

387
00:22:41.029 --> 00:22:45.116
No. I'll debrief David Cartwright
and I'll take a view of the next steps.

388
00:22:45.116 --> 00:22:47.327
which will be an audit
of our identity programs

389
00:22:47.327 --> 00:22:49.162
and a review of our oversight practices.

390
00:22:49.162 --> 00:22:51.414
The conclusions of which
will be made public.

391
00:22:51.414 --> 00:22:55.252
Oh. don't be such a sanctimonious fool.

392
00:22:57.170 --> 00:22:58.004
[stammers]

393
00:22:58.588 --> 00:23:00.674
Uh-- [sighs] I--

394
00:23:02.092 --> 00:23:04.886
You know what. Diana.
I-I will allow you to take that back.

395
00:23:04.886 --> 00:23:08.139
I will take back the tone.
but not the sentiment.

396
00:23:08.848 --> 00:23:13.061
We need to find out
the specifics of what happened

397
00:23:13.061 --> 00:23:15.730
- and if there's going to be another bomb...
- Yeah--

398
00:23:15.730 --> 00:23:18.608
...not call in the management consultants.

399
00:23:18.608 --> 00:23:21.236
You open the books to committees
and journalists and the public.

400
00:23:21.236 --> 00:23:22.320
you never get them out.

401
00:23:22.320 --> 00:23:24.739
And who ends up looking like the bad guys?

402
00:23:24.739 --> 00:23:25.907
Us!

403
00:23:25.907 --> 00:23:27.200
I said elsewhere.

404
00:23:27.200 --> 00:23:29.077
[stammers] Apologies. ma'am.

405
00:23:29.077 --> 00:23:31.079
Adam Lockhead's
bought a ticket back to London.

406
00:23:31.079 --> 00:23:32.080
He's inbound.

407
00:23:32.080 --> 00:23:33.248
[exhales sharply]

408
00:23:57.731 --> 00:24:00.358
[line ringing]

409
00:24:03.445 --> 00:24:04.279
[Flyte] <i>Ma'am.</i>

410
00:24:04.279 --> 00:24:07.324
Flyte. keep one car on course
to pick up David Cartwright

411
00:24:07.324 --> 00:24:09.159
<i>and send the others to St. Pancras.</i>

412
00:24:09.159 --> 00:24:12.913
<i>River Cartwright is coming in from Paris.</i>

413
00:24:12.913 --> 00:24:14.956
- [Flyte] <i>Yes. ma'am. on our way now.</i>
- Sorry.

414
00:24:49.074 --> 00:24:51.409
All right. You-You both go in and get him.

415
00:24:51.993 --> 00:24:53.203
[Chapman] Why us?

416
00:24:53.203 --> 00:24:55.664
Uh-- [sighs] Because he fucking hates me.

417
00:25:12.138 --> 00:25:14.140
[phone buzzes]

418
00:25:15.183 --> 00:25:16.601
[Flyte] <i>Do you have eyes on Cartwright?</i>

419
00:25:16.601 --> 00:25:18.895
Just arrived. Heading in now.

420
00:25:26.570 --> 00:25:27.821
[Chapman] Right. I'll get David.

421
00:25:27.821 --> 00:25:29.406
- No. I'll get David.
- No. you won't.

422
00:25:29.406 --> 00:25:31.616
- You stop the Dogs.
- [scoffs] How am I going to do that?

423
00:25:31.616 --> 00:25:33.034
I don't know. Do something.

424
00:25:33.034 --> 00:25:35.370
I can't do it.
One of them might recognize me.

425
00:25:35.870 --> 00:25:36.871
[sighs]

426
00:25:39.583 --> 00:25:40.584
[Catherine] Mmm.

427
00:25:42.711 --> 00:25:43.712
[Chapman] Sir.

428
00:25:45.463 --> 00:25:46.339
Sorry?

429
00:25:47.591 --> 00:25:48.675
Chapman. sir.

430
00:25:50.010 --> 00:25:51.469
Bad Sam. Remember?

431
00:25:53.930 --> 00:25:56.141
[laughs] God.

432
00:25:56.850 --> 00:25:58.518
Bad Sam.

433
00:25:58.518 --> 00:26:01.187
Well. you were always good to me.

434
00:26:01.187 --> 00:26:02.355
[both laugh]

435
00:26:02.355 --> 00:26:03.440
What are you doing here?

436
00:26:03.440 --> 00:26:04.858
I'll explain while we walk. sir.

437
00:26:04.858 --> 00:26:05.942
Walk where?

438
00:26:06.568 --> 00:26:08.320
I must wait for First Desk.

439
00:26:09.362 --> 00:26:10.196
[sighs]

440
00:26:10.196 --> 00:26:12.282
[sighing]

441
00:26:26.796 --> 00:26:27.797
[door closes]

442
00:26:29.382 --> 00:26:30.217
[grunts]

443
00:26:30.217 --> 00:26:32.844
[alarm blares]

444
00:26:32.844 --> 00:26:33.929
[David] What's that?

445
00:26:34.429 --> 00:26:36.348
- Has there been a breach?
- [Chapman] No. it's just a test. sir.

446
00:26:36.348 --> 00:26:38.433
- Let's go.
- No. no. I-I-I have to wait here.

447
00:26:38.433 --> 00:26:40.644
You don't have to wait. sir.
I'm here to collect you and take you.

448
00:26:40.644 --> 00:26:42.187
No-- Nobody told me that--

449
00:26:42.771 --> 00:26:44.356
[Dog 1] Did you ever work here?

450
00:26:44.356 --> 00:26:45.982
[Dog 2] Yeah.
for the last couple of years.

451
00:26:45.982 --> 00:26:47.317
Falling apart by the end.

452
00:26:47.317 --> 00:26:49.694
[doorman] Excuse me. gents.
If you could just wait here a moment.

453
00:26:49.694 --> 00:26:50.737
Thank you.

454
00:26:50.737 --> 00:26:51.988
You left before I did.

455
00:26:51.988 --> 00:26:53.615
First Desk asked me to collect you. sir.

456
00:26:53.615 --> 00:26:55.200
His office is just back here.

457
00:26:55.200 --> 00:26:56.743
No. it's not. It's on the fifth floor.

458
00:26:56.743 --> 00:26:58.620
[doorman] Apologies.
but an alarm has been triggered.

459
00:26:58.620 --> 00:27:00.163
It may be nothing.
but we have to check it out.

460
00:27:00.163 --> 00:27:02.332
If you could just wait here
till we get the all clear.

461
00:27:02.332 --> 00:27:05.252
Flyte's not gonna like this.
We should go in.

462
00:27:05.252 --> 00:27:06.920
Sorry. sir. MI5.

463
00:27:06.920 --> 00:27:09.172
- Oh. Right. yes. Of course.
- We need access now.

464
00:27:09.839 --> 00:27:11.716
- [David] Why are you here anyway?
- We need to go.

465
00:27:11.716 --> 00:27:13.468
- Now!
- No! I'm waiting for First Desk.

466
00:27:13.468 --> 00:27:15.345
[Chapman] Please.
He's only got a five-minute window.

467
00:27:15.345 --> 00:27:17.389
Five-minute window.
Listen to me. he's standing by...

468
00:27:23.937 --> 00:27:25.438
[Dog 1] We're here for David Cartwright.

469
00:27:30.902 --> 00:27:32.696
- [David] Where are you taking me?
- Here he comes.

470
00:27:32.696 --> 00:27:33.947
Look. he's sent a car for you.

471
00:27:33.947 --> 00:27:35.740
- [Catherine] Hello. David.
- [David] What are you doing here?

472
00:27:35.740 --> 00:27:37.576
- [Catherine] Sit down. There you go.
- [David] What?

473
00:27:37.576 --> 00:27:39.995
When the Park realize I whisked him
away from the Dogs. they'll be after me.

474
00:27:39.995 --> 00:27:42.330
And once they find out what
I did in France. I'm done.

475
00:27:42.330 --> 00:27:44.708
You know.
what happened in France is on him.

476
00:27:44.708 --> 00:27:47.002
Lamb. where are we going? [whimpering]

477
00:27:47.002 --> 00:27:50.463
He's fucking senile. Jackson.
and a legend. Spotless record.

478
00:27:50.463 --> 00:27:51.756
They kicked me out. remember?

479
00:27:51.756 --> 00:27:53.341
Who are they gonna hang this on?

480
00:27:53.341 --> 00:27:55.886
- [David] I-I don't understand. I--
- Where's your flight fund?

481
00:27:55.886 --> 00:27:57.387
- [Catherine] Everything's all right.
- In the office.

482
